PROBLEM: 'The quiz scores of a class with '$k > 12$' students have a mean of '$8$'. The mean of a collection of '$12$' of these quiz scores is '$14$'. What is the mean of the remaining quiz scores in terms of '$k$'?\n'
=======
CHOICES:
[A]: ~\frac{14-8}{k-12}
[B]: ~\frac{8k-168}{k-12}
[C]: ~\frac{14}{12} - \frac{8}{k}
[D]: {k^2}
[E]: {8k}

PROBLEM: 'Chantal and Jean start hiking from a trailhead toward a fire tower. Jean is wearing a heavy backpack and walks slower. Chantal starts walking at '$4$' miles per hour. Halfway to the tower, the trail becomes really steep, and Chantal slows down to '$2$' miles per hour. After reaching the tower, she immediately turns around and descends the steep part of the trail at '$3$" miles per hour. She meets Jean at the halfway point. What was Jean's average speed, in miles per hour, until they meet?\n"
=======
CHOICES:
[A]: ~\frac{12}{13}
[B]: ~1
[C]: ~\frac{13}{12}
[D]: ~\frac{24}{13}
[E]: ~2

PROBLEM: 'Let '$f$' be a function defined on the set of positive rational numbers with the property that '$f(a\cdot b)=f(a)+f(b)$' for all positive rational numbers '$a$' and '$b$'. Suppose that '$f$' also has the property that '$f(p)=p$' for every prime number '$p$'. For which of the following numbers '$x$' is '$f(x)<0$'?\n'
=======
CHOICES:
[A]: \frac{17}{32}
[B]: \frac{11}{16}
[C]: \frac79
[D]: \frac76
[E]: \frac{25}{11}

PROBLEM: 'The interior of a quadrilateral is bounded by the graphs of '$(x+ay)^2 = 4a^2$' and '$(ax-y)^2 = a^2$', where '$a$' is a positive real number. What is the area of this region in terms of '$a$', valid for all '$a > 0$'?\n'
=======
CHOICES:
[A]: ~\frac{8a^2}{(a+1)^2}
[B]: ~\frac{4a}{a+1}
[C]: ~\frac{8a}{a+1}
[D]: ~\frac{8a^2}{a^2+1}
[E]: ~\frac{8a}{a^2+1}
